name: dist/index.js
Reflexor
description: Reflexor Class - A reactive state management library with persistence and batching capabilities.

name: openIndexedDB
description: Opens an IndexedDB connection.

unknown.tagValue: {Promise<IDBDatabase>} A promise that resolves to the database instance.

return.description: A promise that resolves to the database instance.

name: saveToIndexedDB
description: Saves a value to IndexedDB.

unknown.tagValue: {Promise<void>} A promise that resolves when the save is complete.

return.description: A promise that resolves when the save is complete.

name: getFromIndexedDB
description: Retrieves a value from IndexedDB.

unknown.tagValue: {Promise<any>} A promise that resolves to the retrieved value.

return.description: A promise that resolves to the retrieved value.

name: ensureFileExists
description: Ensures that the local storage file exists (Node.js only).

name: saveToFile
description: Saves a value to a file (Node.js only).

name: getFromFile
description: Retrieves a value from a file (Node.js only).

name: saveState
description: Saves a state to the appropriate storage (IndexedDB or file).

unknown.tagValue: {Promise<void>} A promise that resolves when the save operation completes.

return.description: A promise that resolves when the save operation completes.

name: getState
description: Retrieves a state from the appropriate storage (IndexedDB or file).

unknown.tagValue: {Promise<any>} A promise that resolves to the retrieved state value.

return.description: A promise that resolves to the retrieved state value.

name: initialize
description: Initializes Reflexor by loading all persisted states.

unknown.tagValue: {Promise<void>} A promise that resolves when initialization is complete.

return.description: A promise that resolves when initialization is complete.

name: enableBatching
description: Enables batching of state updates.

name: disableBatching
description: Disables batching of state updates.

name: flushBatches
description: Flushes all batched updates, applying them to their respective states.

name: enqueueTransaction
description: Queues a transaction to ensure concurrency safety.

unknown.tagValue: {Promise<T>} A promise that resolves when the transaction is complete.

return.description: A promise that resolves when the transaction is complete.

name: setLogger
description: Sets a custom logger for debugging.

name: log
description: Logs a message at the specified level.

params.name: args
params.description: The message and arguments to log.

name: reflex
description: Creates a new reactive state.

unknown.tagValue: {ReactiveState} A proxy object representing the reactive state.

params.name: initialValue
params.description: The initial value of the state.

params.name: key
params.description: Optional key for persisting the state.

return.description: A proxy object representing the reactive state.

name: getReflexValue
description: Retrieves the current value of a reactive state.

unknown.tagValue: {any} The current value of the state.

return.description: The current value of the state.

name: hasReflex
description: Checks if a reactive state exists.

unknown.tagValue: {boolean} True if the state exists, false otherwise.

return.description: True if the state exists, false otherwise.

name: removeReflex
description: Removes a reactive state, including its persisted data if applicable.

name: getAllReflexes
description: Retrieves all reactive states.

unknown.tagValue: {Map<any, ReactiveState>} A map of all reactive states.

return.description: A map of all reactive states.

name: clearAllReflexes
description: Clears all reactive states, including persisted data if applicable.

name: getStateCount
description: Returns the total count of active reactive states.

name: addMiddleware
description: Adds a middleware function to process state updates.

name: applyMiddlewares
description: Applies all middleware functions to a state value.

unknown.tagValue: {any} The processed value after applying all middleware.

return.description: The processed value after applying all middleware.

name: setValueWithMiddleware
description: Sets the value of a reactive state after applying middleware.

name: onReflexChange
description: Registers a listener for changes to the value of one or more reactive states.

params.name: listener
params.description: The function to be called when a state value changes.

params.name: states
params.description: An array of reactive state proxies to listen to.

name: onReflexDrop
description: Registers a listener for when one or more reactive states are removed.

params.name: listener
params.description: The function to be called when a state is removed.

params.name: states
params.description: An array of reactive state proxies to listen to.

name: onReflexReset
description: Registers a listener for when one or more reactive states are reset to their initial values.

params.name: listener
params.description: The function to be called when a state is reset.

params.name: states
params.description: An array of reactive state proxies to listen to.

name: reset
description:
Resets a reactive state to its initial value.
Triggers listeners for both value changes and resets.

params.name: state
params.description: The reactive state proxy to reset.
